Title: J- 40/20s: 5 x 5 min
WorkoutDescription: 2 hr total with 40/20s, I've borrowed this one form TP Training library but its similar in theme to the alternating hills that you've done. its intended on the flat road, but a slight uphill would be fine. roll back between the 5. The rest of what you read is TP description- i've left the blurb for your perusal. this is a 'classic' top end set for cyclists. Drives up power at V02max, improves lactate tolerance and consequently also pulls threshold up from above. Warm Up: 20-30' endurance riding and a 5' progression effort to threshold. 5' easy then get into it. Main Session: 40/20s - 40s on / ~130% Threshold (~5'max power) - Really just as hard as you can sustain across the whole session. If you can do more and not drop power till the end, then do it. - 20s off / easy pedalling - 4:40 easy between sets - RPE: 9-10/10 by the end. Fuelling: 60g/hr carbs
